Notes on how to build Python wheels

1) Configure libFAUDES

Choose a sensible set of plugins and be sure to exclude luabindings. Example:

./libFAUDES> make dist-clean
./libFAUDES> make -j configure FAUDES_PLUGINS="synthesis omegaaut pybindings"


2) Prepare Pyhton project folder

We want a selfcontained project as follows

pyproj -+ pyproject.toml
        + setup.py
	+ faudes.py    (as generated by SWIG)
	+ src/*        (all C++ files incl headers required to sompile
	+ MANIFEST.in  (declare files that go to sdist, i.e., all)
	+ README.md
	+ LICENSE

This is currently included in "make configure"


3) Run Python for a local build with the host as taget

Get the Python packages "build" and "setuptools"

./pyproj> python -m build

Test the result with

./pyproj> pip install dist/XYZ.whl

Publish result with

python3 -m twine upload --repository testpypi dist/*

Install test wheel

python3 -m pip install --index-url https://test.pypi.org/simple/ faudes


4) Prepare for  cross-platform

Get the Python package "cibuildwheel" and test with e.g.

./pyproj> cibuildwheel --platform linux 

This requires a docker daemon, e.g., DockerDesktop


5) Do all

See build.wheels.yml
